===Etymology===
First coined  1382, from Middle English “zele”, from Old French “zel”, from Late Latin “zēlus”, from {{etyl|grc}} {{term|ζήλος||zeal, jealousy|trans=zēlos|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}} < {{term|ζηλόω||to emulate, to be jealous|trans=zēloō|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# The [[fervor]] or tireless [[devotion]] for a person, cause, or ideal and determination in its furtherance; [[diligent]] [[enthusiasm]]; [[powerful]] [[interest]].

